                        <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d4"><locus target="#iiv(erso)" facs="003">Fol. iiv(erso)</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1066DavidHarp">David Playing the Harp</ref></desc></decoNote>
                        <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d5"><locus target="#146r" facs="148">Fol. 146r</locus><desc>Portrait of the owner Ǝğğǝgu Nǝguśe and his wife, Zäwditu, and other family members,  with caption (top to bottom): <q> “How Ato Ǝğğǝgu and Wäyzäro Zäwditu prayed and said, ‘the things of this world are temporary and may He prepare the heavenly place,’” “Aräfu,” “Fäläqäč,” “Ada Ayäläč,”  “how Wäyzäro Zäwditu pleaded by the name of Mary."</q></desc></decoNote>
                        <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d6"><locus target="#146v" facs="149">Fol. 146v</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1031VirginAndChild">Virgin and Child</ref> with <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS3827Ephrem">St Ephrem the Syrian</persName>, with caption <q>“How Ephrem, [the Syrian,] has praised our Lady Mary.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                        <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d7">
                          Decorative designs:
                          <locus target="#1r #8v #16v #25r #36r #44v #51r #60v #72r #80v #86r #98v #110v #114r #120r #126v #139r #147r" facs="003 011 019 027 038 047 053 063 074 083 088 101 113 116 122 129 141 149">folss. 1r, 8v, 16v, 25r, 36r, 44v, 51r, 60v, 72r, 80v, 86r, 98v, 110v, 114r, 120r, 126v, 139r, 147r, </locus> (multi-colored ornate ḥaräg);
                          <locus target="#8r #16r #44r #60r #80r #85v #164r" facs="010 018 046 062 082 088 166">8r, 16r, 44r, 60r, 80r, 85v, 164r, </locus> (multiple full stops);
                          <locus target="#126r" facs="128">126r</locus> (multiple full stops connected by alternating black and red dotted lines</decoNote>
                        </decoDesc>
                        <additions><list>
                        <item xml:id="a1"><desc type="OwnershipNote"><locus target="#164r" facs="166">Fol. 164r</locus> <q>Ǝğğǝgu Nǝguśe. Copied by ‘Aläqa ‘Aynä ‘Aläm, from Däbrä Wärq where [the famous] icon called Wäynut is located. Written in the reign of Mark [the Evangelist], Mäggabit 8, 1914 EC.  Bless God who helped me to finish with health and peace.”</q>
                        <q><foreign xml:lang="gez">ዝዳዊት፡ ዘእጅጉ፡ ንጉሤ፡ ዘአጽሐፎ፡ ወጸሐፊሁኒ፡ አለቃ፡ ዓይነ፡ ዓለም፡ ወስመ፡ ሀገሮሙ፡ ደብረ፡ ወርቅ፡ እንተ፡ ባቲ፡ ስእለ፡ ማርያም፡ ወይኑት፡ ዘመነ፡ ማርቆስ መጋቢት:፰ ቀን፡ ፲፱፻፲፬ ዓመት፡ ተጽሕፈ፡ ይትባረክ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ዘአፈጸመኒ፡ በዳኅና፡ ወበሰላም፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን።</foreign></q></desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e1"><desc><locus target="#164v" facs="167">Fol. 164v</locus> blank</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e2"><desc>Binding is original, intact, and in excellent condition</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e3"><desc>Vellum is clean and intact, in very good condition</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="a2"><desc type="StampExlibris"><locus target="#Seal">Fols. Seal, </locus>
                        Ǝğğǝgu Nǝguśe 1916 (E.C.): <locus target="#1r #8v #16v #25r #36r #44v #51r #60v #72r #80v #86r #98v #110v #114r #120r #126r #139r #145v #147r #164r" facs="003 011 019 027 038 047 053 063 074 083 088 101 113 116 122 128 141 148 149 166">1r, 8v, 16v, 25r, 36r, 44v, 51r, 60v, 72r, 80v, 86r, 98v, 110v, 114r, 120r, 126r, 139r, 145v, 147r, 164r</locus></desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e4"><desc>Numbered quires: quires 2–14</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e5"><desc>
                          words of text are written interlinearly, <locus target="#2v #14r #22v #141v" facs="005 016 025 144">folss. 2v, 14r, 22v, 141v, </locus>;
                          and lines of text are written interlinearly, <locus target="#64r #74v #79r #92v" facs="066 077 081 095">64r, 74v, 79r, 92v, </locus>, etc.;
                          erasure markings are visible, <locus target="#15v #17r #20r" facs="018 019 022">15v, 17r, 20r, </locus>, etc.;
                          text has been removed, e.g., <locus target="#55v #144v" facs="058 147">55v, 144v</locus></desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e7"><desc>The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the
                          selection of an appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too
                          long, the scribe reduces the font size at the end of lines to avoid having to go onto the next line (e.g., <locus target="#2v #6r #7v #8r" facs="005 008 010 010">folss. 2v, 6r, 7v, 8r, </locus>). This scribe also
                          will complete the line of text above or below the end of the line, e.g., <locus target="#2v #7r #7v #24v" facs="005 009 010 027">2v, 7r, 7v, 24v</locus>
                        </desc></item>
                        </list></additions>
